remarks: The purpose of the survey was to evaluate the panfish population. Anglers are complaining about the small panfish. Bluegills could stand heavy selective treatment.

point_of_examination: Launching of the boat to set the nets was from the old Ketchel place now belonging to Mr. Dubois
remarks: Purpose of survey was to check present fish population and in particular to check northern pike abundance. Comments from residents and our catch results indicate pike numbers are way down. Several residents were surprised at the small size of the blue bluegills in our catch. They said what they caught (con't on back) were larger. I've fished this lake and I agree with them. Northern Pike if planted in small sizes may not fare well in presence of reported mud pickerel population. Recommend no further management of this lake at this time.

After a virtual absence of bluegills in previous surveys, it now appears a large crop is approaching a desirable catchable size. Saw 4-5 - 5 nice largemouth bass while setting nets but caught none during the survey.
Three walleyes taken. Some nice yellow perch are located here.
Catch summary of Lake Macatawa Survey.

point_of_examination: State access site on north shore
remarks: One white bass taken here. Numerous gizzard shad. Five walleyes taken.

Little evidence of fishing. Two anglers were attempting to catch gold shiners for use as bait at another lake. Channel to main body of lake is very weed choked.

point_of_examination: Randomly from Public Access site on south shore.
remarks: Survey to evaluate the 1977 spring partial treatment on the panfish. There has been vast improvement in the size range of panfish as compared to pretreatment time.

Survey in conjunction with selective treatment program. Many pike taken but very skinny. Panfish good size and appear healthy as do the bass. 3-4 bluegills sampled were very pale. Sunfish-bluegill hybridizing noted. Yellow-brown bullhead also look hybridized.
Bluegills appear small and stunted. Several large largemouth bass were observed on the beds. A selective treatment with antimycin is recommended.
comments: remarks also say small and stunted

remarks: Largemouth bass were in excellent condition. Bluegills were small. Fishermen complained about small panfish present.
48 hours each for 2 trapnets and 2 fykenets
Bluegill growth and average size has substantially increased, following selective treatment program. Fish are in excellent condition.

gear_used_kind: 2 gill nets, 3 fyke nets & 3 trap nets
remarks: Evaluation of partial treatment program. The quality of the bluegill fishing has improved spectacularly since inception of the partial treatment program with the chemical antimycin.

Selective treatment program is working well. Found many large (6-8") healthy bluegills with "shoulders" and big "slab" crappies. Fish appear to be moving into the shallows. Good survey but nets didn't fish as well as expected.
Survey was in conjunction with the selective treatment program. Panfish appear to be doing well in spite of many small ones present. Selective treatment program is holding up well.

Panfish growth appears to be improving. Average size of bluegills has increased considerably since selective treatment program. Small panfish are in evidence. Northern pike year classes are impressive. Additional northern pike plants are recommended.
Survey was follow-up to selective treatment program. Improvements in panfish average size being seen.
Survey was done to evaluate a 1967 partial treatment. Bluegills appear small and stunted. Further partial treatment program is recommended.
This survey was conducted to evaluate the selective treatment program. Panfish are in good condition.
Heavy population of small bluegills - may need thinning. Tiger muskies may not be moving well this time of year as only three were taken.
Yellow perch very large and numerous. Bluegill fishing reported to be good with large ones being taken. Eight fishing boats were on the lake 9:00 AM 7-27-71.
Fishermen report catching many 6"+ bluegills. Bass fishing has declined somewhat in recent years.
Survey was done to check for the presence of walleyes from previous plants for rearing purposes. Bluegills in good condition. Walleyes relatively abundant.
NA
Bluegills and tiger muskies growing well and in good condition. No evidence of reproduction in muskies. All goldfish observed were large indicating the muskies are utilizing them for forage.
Tiger muskies planted on top of goldfish fish population in 1969. Growth of these fish has been excellent. The fish averaged 8.8'' when planted 8/6/69. Bluegills are stunted.
NA
fish appear very healthy and show good size. Survey was to evaluate selective treatment program.
Survey was done to evaluate selective treatment program. Few fish were taken. Two nets had been opened or broken into. I recommend additional netting at a later date.
Survey was done to evaluate selective treatment program. Panfish appear to be somewhat larger and more robust.
From this survey, the panfish seem in excellent condition. The selective treatment program remains successful.

point_of_examination: S end of lake & E side just N of island
remarks: Bob Davey set 2 nets by himself. Although they were set tight and straight (quite a job with one hand!), they were fished very poorly. Many aquatic weeds on ropes and anchors after 1 night set. Selective treatment program evaluation. Enough were observed to indicate needing another partial. Additional comments on back Comments: con't. 1970 - Bluegills stunting - growth indexes negative by more than 1" for all ages sampled. 1974 - One year after 1st antimycin partial. All age classes checked equal or exceed state avg. growth rates. 1978 - 3 years after last antimycin partial. Growth indexes range from -0.1 to +0.5", not as good as 1974 but still far better than in 1970.

Except for bullheads the catch was small. Dense growths of aquatic vegetation in depths suitable for out [sic] netting gear is suspected as the cause for the poor results. The catch certainly does not support the fine pondfish fish angling reports we believe to be true.
Follow-up to selective treatment program. Bluegill average size improving. Program appears. Program appears successful.

remarks: This net fished 11 net nights in the same location. All of the smallmouth bass were tagged. Set location is marked on the attached map.

remarks: Abundance of small bluegills; game fish are lacking. Fishermen report catching occasional bass but success decreasing yearly. Perhaps needs partial treatment and stocking of bass.
Set nets to catch big bluegill and largemouth bass, but apparently fish are in deep water. Fishermen reported catching small bluegills. Further work needed.

remarks: A surprising good collection of game and panfish with relatively few rough fish. Nearly all the pumpkinseeds and most of the bluegills seemed to belong to just a few year classes as if other years reproduction was unsuccessful.

remarks: Many small bass fry were observed on 10-8 around this net - 1.5 - 2" long.
A few residents complained of small bluegills and perch. Lake is quite shallow but does not winterkill. Maximum depth is 10 to 12 ft. May require additional predator stocking.
Survey is in conjunction with Selective Treatment Program. Our survey results show a reduction of the average size for panfish from last year's data. Smaller fish are more abundant.
Survey is follow-up to selective treatment program. Bl Large Bluegills show growth improvements. . Large spawning white suckers were present on NW shoreline. . Bluegills fishing is excellent. .
This sheet is separate from the trap and gill net sheet because these nets are size selective and it would give an inappropriate value for species averages.

depth_of_collection: 4 - 4-6' for trapnets nets and 4 - 4-25' for gill nets
remarks: The lake was very clear with hard bottom be sure to set the lead anchor securely. Large gravel bar at SE corner of lake contains a few large shallow boulders that should be marked for boating safety.
Trout survival is evident. 1972 lake trout plants are still in evidence. Good yellow perch population.

point_of_examination: various points over lake - entire lake
area_covered: whole lake, set 1 night, ran, set second night and pulled
remarks: General lake survey. 5 trout taken, 2 lakers, 3 rainbows. Rock bass 2nd most numerous fish taken, black crappies #1. Rock bass very fat; crappies thin. No size to SMB, bluegills mostly small; caught some 8"ers in 30' deep gill net.
Good perch population, providing good winter fishing. Panfishing has been good in the past.

gear_used_kind: 2 trap nets, 2 fyke nets, 2 gill nets
remarks: Bluegills look good. Several residents reported good fishing for nice sized bluegills and black crappies this year. Also a report of good sized yellow perch being caught. From our survey, northern pike fishing should be good too.

gear_used_kind: 2 trap nets, 2 fyke nets, 2 exp. gill nets
remarks: The purpose of the survey was a general inventory of the fish population. People were complaining about small panfish; however, the results of the survey indicate a desirable fish population exists at this time. No management recommended.

Survey was a general fisheries inventory. Trap nets set 2 nights, gill nets 1 night. All fish look good. Chestnut lamprey found on white sucker. One of the two water intakes found in this lake. Abundance of carp and suckers.

Survey was a general fisheries inventory. Trap nets set 2 nights; gill nets 1 night. All fish look good. Pike had fresh lamprey scar, the other of two intakes found in 2nd lake. Abundance of carp and suckers.
Bluegills plump for their size. Easiest lake of chain to set trap nets in. Bass, pike look healthy. Bullheads abundant. Survey was a general fisheries inventory.
All fish looked good; abundance of carp and suckers. Survey was a general fisheries inventory.
Good population of large bass. Many smaller northern pike present. The pike were in a spent condition.
Fish population looks good pending age and growth studies, especially the bluegill gill and crappies. Did not find any of the young walleyes planted earlier in the season.

gear_used_kind: 2 experimental gills, 10 minnow fykes, 3 trap nets, 3 fykes
remarks: Used minnow nets to find young walleyes from spring fry stocking but were unsuccessful. Also general survey was obtained. Further attempts to capture walleye will be made in the spring of 1979. Fish populations in good condition.

point_of_examination: Sets were made at selected locations to survey the entire lake.
gear_used_kind: 2 trap nets, 2 fyke nets, 2 exp. gill
remarks: Cottage owners complained of carp, but none were taken in nets. A nice size range of bluegills averaging over 6 inches was revealed. Looks like one of our better fishing lakes at this time. No management is recommended at this time.
